													<h3><span class="ertext">See Class Sections Below</span></h3>
												
													 PREREQUISITES:<br> Prerequisites are strictly enforced for all Math
 courses. For more information, please refer to the
 UCSD Course Catalog.<br> <br> MATH PLACEMENT EXAM:<br> Entering students must take the Math Placement Exam
 (MPE) prior to registration unless they have one of the
 following: appropriate score on an AP calculus AB or BC
 exam: appropriate score on the SAT II Math Level 2
 exam: appropriate  score on the IB Higher Level Math
 exam: credit by means of a foreign exam (e.g. GCE):
 transferable  college credit in Calculus.<br> <br> Please note: Transferable pre-calculus courses DO NOT
 satisfy any UCSD math course prerequisites.<br> <br> For information on the Math Placement Exam go to the
 <a href="http://mathtesting.ucsd.edu/">
 Math Testing and Placement website</a>.<br> <br> TRANSFER COURSES<br> For a list of transfer-equivalent math courses offered
 at California community colleges, CSUs, and other UC
 campuses, please visit the following website:
 <a href="https://tinyurl.com/4czc9xay">
 Transfer Equivalencies </a>.<br> <br> PLANNED COURSE OFFERINGS<br> For a list of current and upcoming planned course
 offerings, please visit <a href="https://tinyurl.com/yzvthjah">
 COURSE OFFERINGS</a>.<br> <br> TEXTBOOKS<br> Students with questions about their lower-division
 textbooks should go to:
 <a href="https://tinyurl.com/2p86fhe5">
 Textbook Information </a>.
 MATLAB COURSES:<br> Math 20D and 18 have a lab component using computer
 software (MATLAB) to further explore the material and
 applications of topics in class.  For information
 please go to:<br><br> <a href="https://mathweb.ucsd.edu/~math20d/"> Math 20D</a><br>
 <a href="https://mathweb.ucsd.edu/~math18m/"> Math 18</a><br> <br> For any questions please use the
 <a href="https://vac.ucsd.edu">
 Virtual Advising Center</a>.
